---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [
  { href: "#latest", label: "Latest" },
  { href: "#archive", label: "Topics" },
  { href: "#about", label: "About" },
];
const navCta = { href: "#subscribe", label: "Subscribe →" };
---

<Layout variant="flagship-observability">
  <Nav variant="flagship-observability" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

  <header class="masthead">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="masthead-label">Phidea</div>
      <h1>What's actually happening with AI in insurance. <em>Weekly.</em></h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Every Tuesday morning: the regulator moves, the model updates, the carrier experiments, and the ones that didn't make it past compliance review. Written for people who read combined ratios before they read keynote slides.
      </p>

      <form action="https://buttondown.email/api/emails/embed-subscribe/phidea" method="POST" class="signup">
        <input type="hidden" name="tag" value="flagship-observability" />
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required />
        <button type="submit">Subscribe →</button>
      </form>
      <p class="signup-small">One email per week. Unsubscribe in one click. No sales pitch.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section id="latest" class="latest">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Recent briefs</div>

      <article class="brief">
        <div class="brief-meta">Topic · Compliance</div>
        <h3>Colorado's SB21-169 Q1 filings: who demonstrated the quantitative test, who deferred, and why it matters for every other state.</h3>
        <p>The Colorado DOI's life filings are the first real-world read on whether carriers can produce a passing test at operational cadence. Proxy-variable detection, not demographic calibration, looks like the blocker. The adopters' patterns are worth studying before NAIC extends the framework.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="brief">
        <div class="brief-meta">Topic · Model operations</div>
        <h3>OpenAI ships silent model updates. Carriers should fingerprint behavior, not just track version numbers.</h3>
        <p>Behavioral fingerprints across four providers show refusal-rate shifts on personal-lines coverage questions without corresponding version-number changes. The drift is real, invisible to naive version tracking, and catches carriers who relied on provider-published model cards.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="brief">
        <div class="brief-meta">Topic · Distribution</div>
        <h3>A governed Custom GPT in a regulated line: where compliance will hold the launch, and how to prevent it.</h3>
        <p>The IDD advice-boundary classifier is the single most common hold. Price-accuracy checks are second. Post-processor disclosure injection is third. All three are solvable before legal review, and the deployment pattern is replicable across life, P&amp;C, and health.</p>
      </article>

      <p class="latest-more"><a href="#archive">See all topics</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="archive" class="archive">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Topics we track</div>
      <h2>Eighteen angles. Four tiers of reader.</h2>
      <p class="archive-lead">
        Each topic page is a short brief with five things to check. Jump to the tier that matches your week.
      </p>

      <div class="tier-grid">
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Tier 1 · Distribution</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/ai-visibility.html">Be present when buyers ask AI for insurance</a></li>
            <li><a href="/competitor-share.html">See who ChatGPT mentions instead of you</a></li>
            <li><a href="/custom-gpt.html">Ship a Custom GPT compliance can live with</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ai-channel.html">Count the business AI assistants send you</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ai-attribution.html">Trace each AI conversation to the policy it bound</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Tier 2 · AI operations</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/ai-monitoring.html">Know what your AI agents said last night</a></li>
            <li><a href="/model-drift.html">Catch vendor model updates before a customer does</a></li>
            <li><a href="/hallucination-guardrail.html">Stop a made-up coverage answer before delivery</a></li>
            <li><a href="/audit-bundle.html">Have a regulator bundle ready, every quarter</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Tier 3 · Compliance</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/regulator-mapping.html">Six AI rulebooks, one mapping</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ais-program.html">The AIS Program regulators expect</a></li>
            <li><a href="/adverse-decision-trail.html">Explain every adverse AI decision, statutorily</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ecdis-oversight.html">Track every third-party data source your models touch</a></li>
            <li><a href="/bias-testing.html">Protected-class testing, per state, continuously</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Tier 4 · Model risk</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/mrm-llms.html">Govern LLMs under the MRM framework you already have</a></li>
            <li><a href="/predictive-monitoring.html">Watch pricing drift between reserves reviews</a></li>
            <li><a href="/augmented-underwriting.html">Give underwriters their three hours back</a></li>
            <li><a href="/portfolio-drift.html">See portfolio drift before the quarterly deck</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="subscribe" class="subscribe-strip">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Phidea Weekly</div>
      <h2>One email. Every Tuesday. Free.</h2>
      <p>Written for people who have to make the call by Friday.</p>
      <form action="https://buttondown.email/api/emails/embed-subscribe/phidea" method="POST" class="signup">
        <input type="hidden" name="tag" value="flagship-observability" />
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required />
        <button type="submit">Subscribe →</button>
      </form>
      <p class="signup-small">Unsubscribe in one click. No sales pitch. No sponsored content.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="about" class="about-strip">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Who writes this</div>
      <p>Phidea is a small team tracking AI in insurance across carriers, surfaces, and regulators. We work with a handful of carriers on AI governance and publish publicly what we see across the rest of the industry. No guest posts. No ghost-writing. No sponsored content.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .wrap-narrow { max-width: 680px; padding-left: 24px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .masthead {
    padding: 96px 0 64px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .masthead-label {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .masthead h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 52px;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .masthead h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .masthead .lead {
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 40px;
  }

  .signup {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 520px;
  }
  .signup input[type=email] {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: inherit;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .signup button {
    padding: 14px 24px;
    border: none;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: inherit;
  }
  .signup button:hover { background: var(--accent); }
  .signup-small {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .latest { padding: 72px 0 48px; }
  .brief {
    padding: 28px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .brief:first-of-type { padding-top: 8px; }
  .brief:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
  .brief-meta {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .brief h3 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .brief p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .latest-more {
    margin-top: 32px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .latest-more a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .latest-more a:hover { color: var(--ink); }

  .archive {
    padding: 72px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--soft);
  }
  .archive h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .archive-lead {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 40px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .tier-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
  }
  .tier {
    padding: 20px 24px;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 14px;
  }
  .tier-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .tier ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .tier li {
    padding: 10px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .tier li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .tier li a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.45;
    display: block;
  }
  .tier li a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .subscribe-strip {
    padding: 96px 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .subscribe-strip .section-label { justify-content: center; display: inline-block; }
  .subscribe-strip h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 40px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .subscribe-strip p {
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 17px;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }
  .subscribe-strip .signup { margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }

  .about-strip {
    padding: 72px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--soft);
  }
  .about-strip p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .masthead h1 { font-size: 34px; }
    .masthead .lead { font-size: 17px; }
    .signup { flex-direction: column; }
    .brief h3 { font-size: 20px; }
    .tier-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .archive h2 { font-size: 28px; }
    .subscribe-strip h2 { font-size: 28px; }
  }
</style>
